item.title: Relationship between Household Income and Living Provinces
item.description: Abstract: We investigated the data collected from the 2019 Canadian Election Study Online Survey. After a series of careful analyses, the results show that provinces with more people living in having a higher and more stable total household income. This is a significant outcome since it can provide suggestions to people who are hesitating about the location for life and work. Introduction Canada is a wealthy country, though salaries are always dependent on the level of skill, location, and job industry.
